{"lemma":"ذَيْلُ","slug":"ذَيْلُ","root":"ذ.#.ل","root_slug":"ذ-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14224"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to furnish with an appendix, to add a supplement, to provide [+direct object] at the end with [+بِ (object)], to extend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have a sequel or aftereffect، to not end, to continue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lower part of a thing, touching the ground"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tail"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"skirt, hem, train, trail"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fringes"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"appendix, supplement, postscript"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lower margin of a book"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shelter, protection"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ذ ي ل (ḏ y l), an augment of the root ذ ل ل (ḏ l l), meaning \"to be low\", \"to be in low-esteem\". The sense of \"a shelter or protection\" stems from the use of this root to describe weaker tribes that needed the support of stronger allies; contrasted with و ل ي (w l y)."},"ipa":["/ðajl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14224","headword_ar":"ذَيْلٌ","root":"*yl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kindmost, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (M, K.) Accord. to MF, this is the proper signification, and the other significations here following are tropical. (TA.) [But in my opinion, the word in each of the next two senses, or at least in the former of them; if not strictly proper, is what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqiyqapN Eurofiy~apN","text_ar":"حَقِيقَةٌ عُرْفِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. a word so much used in a tropical sense as to be, in that sense, conventionally regarded as proper.] ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A skirt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reaching nearly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quite, to the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is dragged upon the ground, when made to hang down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is next the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if not touching it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as well as if touching it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; an inf. n. used in this sense: (Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a waist-wrapper ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and of a garment [of any kind],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is dragged"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is made to hang down:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of a [garment of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is made to hang down, and touches the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any kind of garment worn by a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that the wearer drags upon the ground behind her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parts, all round,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman's garment,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that fall upon the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion that is made"},{"kind":"page_break","n":991},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to hang down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman's shift and of her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qinaAE","text_ar":"قِنَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or head-covering]: you do not [properly] say of a man that he has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ayol","text_ar":"ذَيْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but only when you liken the lower part of his garment to the similar part of a woman's garment]: a man's having a long garment, such as a shirt and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or his dragging the skirt thereof,] is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_irofaAlN","text_ar":"اـِرْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Khálid Ibn-Jembeh, T:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ayolN","text_ar":"ذَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in this sense, T, Msb, as relating to a shirt [&c.], S, and in all its senses, T, M) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oyaAlN","text_ar":"اَذْيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oyulN","text_ar":"اَذْيُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Hejeree, M, K) [both pls. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uyuwlN","text_ar":"ذُيُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K) which is a pl. of mult. (M.) Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwlu Al*~ayoli","text_ar":"طُولُ الذَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a metonymical expression meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Richness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because long"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oyaAl","text_ar":"اَذْيَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally pertain to the rich and the prodigal and the proud and self-conceited: (Er-Rázee, Har p. 493:) and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAla *ayolu fulaAnK","text_ar":"طَالَ ذَيْلُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of such a one became good, and his wealth became abundant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Tawiylu Al*~ayoli","text_ar":"هُوَ طَوِيلُ الذَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is rich."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 319.) ―         -b3-  Of a horse (T, K) &c., (K,) [i. e.] of a horse and a camel and the like, (M,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail when long:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part, of the tail, that is made to hang down."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b4-  [(assumed tropical:)  Of a cloud, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skirt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower, pendent, part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense in the K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayodabN","text_ar":"هَيْدَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ayolu Alr~iyHi","text_ar":"ذَيْلُ الرِّيحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is dragged along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drawn together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the wind, upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, O, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rubbish:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what the wind leaves upon the sand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the form of a rope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the track of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ayol","text_ar":"ذَيْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skirt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dragged along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oyaAluAlr~iyHi","text_ar":"اَذْيَالُالرِّيحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the after-parts of the wind, with which it sweeps what is light to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ayolu jabalK","text_ar":"ذَيْلُ جَبَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The foot, bottom, base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest part, of a mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A and TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~N","text_ar":"جَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oyaAlu Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"اَذْيَالُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hindmost of the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a A^a*oyaAlN mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ اَذْيَالٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Some few of the hindmost of the people came."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Sgh.) ―         -b8-  See also 2.       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAy^ilN","text_ar":"ذَايِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","M","K","Lth","T","S","TA","O"]}]}}